Messages.Content:
Default GameObject Tag: MainCamera already registered

This is a double-initialization symptom. Something is calling the “register default GO tags” path more than once (common causes: two bootstraps, or a system doing “ensure” without an idempotency guard, or it runs both in baking + runtime, or multiple worlds).

Fix pattern (do this once, globally, per process):

Put the registration behind a single managed gate:

static class DefaultTagRegistryGuard
{
    static bool _done;
    public static bool TryEnter()
    {
        if (_done) return false;
        _done = true;
        return true;
    }
}


Then in whatever code logs “already registered”:

if (!DefaultTagRegistryGuard.TryEnter())
    return;

// register tags...


If tags are meant to be per-world, then gate by world instead:

store a singleton component like DefaultTagsRegistered and early-out if it exists.

This is worth fixing before Linux because it usually means “some init runs twice” and the next thing you double-init is not harmless.

